VSujanaranjani, featured a recital by master Prachothan from Hyderabad.Prachothan began the concert with Saverivarnam,Sarasudain Trisranadaiwith good control on thelaya.Ninne bhajanaof Thyagaraja in Natai was next with a briefaalapand was rendered well.Endundi vedalithivoin Darbar was taken next before going for a detailed Anandabhairaviragamwhich was sung with a good feel.Nee Balma,a rarekrithiof Thyagaraja was boldly attempted.Simhendra madyamawas taken for a detailed essay of theragaand Prachothan did well to sing theraga bhavamwith good feel. He sangPamarajanan paliniof Deekshitar withneraval,which was amazing. Theswarakalpanareflected his passion towards music.Garuda gamanain Nagaswaravali was sung before going to the main piece of the concert.Ragam Tanam Pallaviwas chosen and he sangKokilapriyawhich is a difficultragamto handle.   Thepallaviset to Misra Chaputalamin Tisra nadai was a treat to watch. His timing was perfect and he sang with confidence in the lower and higher octaves.A special mention is to be made about Master Aravind who  did extremely well on the mridangam. Histaniin the complextalawas great for his age.Finally, Prachothan concluded his recital with a Surdas abhang and a thillana in Pahadi. It was amazing to watch these kids perform. They only have to sustain this right attitude to music.
